snippet.textDisplay: Okay, hear me out. What if Theros' Underworld suppresses your "abilities" when your "dead" you become an Returned and you forfeit them; in conclusion, Elspeth was still a Planeswalker, but her spark was placed into dormancy, hence the flash of light, her spark reigniting due to Sparks being perfectly capable of saving the owner. snippet.textDisplay: I know Djawadi didn’t do this on purpose (or did he?) but the music cue that is sung once and then played by violin is very close to the theme of Elspeth as we heard it in the Journey into Nyx trailer. I was simply furious when Elspeth died in Godsend and even though I knew she was not fully gone, I still lamented her death. With her back in Theros Beyond Death I am overjoyed to see my old friend back, a little different but death will bring change..
